// Adaptive Spliting iterator, method stealing 1 (-smethodStealing=1) 
// Initially it distributes the ranges to split among the threads (tasks)
// Then it performs Binary Splitting localy on each thread
// When a Threads exhausts its local range, it steals and splits from another thread (victim)
// If it has sucess on the stealing, it chooses another victim and tries to steal again.
// The Splitting method on the stealed thread can be Binary
// The Termination strategy is still very naive

// Contributed by Angeles Navarro 
use DynamicIters;
extern proc usleep(val:uint);
